            <head>
              <title type="main">Outside the Toronto Art Gallery</title>
            </head>
            <p>“Mysticism isn’t my thing and I pay very little attention to it.”—a Gentleman near
“The Vision of Ezekiel”</p>
            <p>I saw the spirit of William Blake today while on my way to his big show
<q>
shining through<lb/>
the black eyes<lb/>
of a saucy squirrel
</q>
black furred as the black bear was this creature poised at the gate
<q>
tiny animal hand<lb/>
articulated<lb/>
against<lb/>
the stone wall
</q>
he looked me long in the eye
<q>
the Sun<lb/>
focused<lb/>
there<lb/>
<lb/>
a moment passed<lb/>
then off he dashed<lb/>
to terrorize<lb/>
just for fun<lb/>
a flock<lb/>
of complacent<lb/>
birds<lb/>
<lb/>
into the sky<lb/>
they rose<lb/>
as one
</q></p>
